Senate Commerce and Labor 2
Amendment No. 2 to SB0865
Bailey
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 865 House Bill No. 705*
by deleting SECTION 2 and substituting:
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-104(b)(10), is amended by
deleting "portable electronics insurance" and substituting "portable electronics or optical
products insurance".
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-110(8), is amended by deleting
the subdivision and substituting:
(8) Portable electronics or optical products insurance; or
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101(2), is amended by
deleting "purchases portable electronics or services" and substituting "purchases portable
electronics, optical products, or services".
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101(4), is amended by
deleting "portable electronics" wherever it appears and substituting "portable electronics or
optical products".
SECTION 6. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101(6), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting:
(6) "Portable electronics":
(A) Means equipment that is portable in nature, has electrical, digital,
magnetic, wireless, optical, electromagnetic, or similar capabilities, which operate
using batteries, rechargeable power sources, or other energy sources; and
(B) Includes:
(i) Equipment that:
SA1010
015411
- 1 -

(a) Is used for communication, data processing, viewing,
listening, recording, gaming, computing, navigation, household,
health or activity monitoring, or similar uses; and
(b) May incorporate features responsive to user input or
environmental conditions; and
(ii) Accessories and services related to the use of the equipment;
SECTION 7. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101(7), is amended by
deleting "Portable electronics insurance" wherever it appears and substituting "Portable
electronics or optical products insurance"; and deleting "portable electronics" wherever it
appears and substituting "portable electronics or optical products".
SECTION 8. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101(8), is amended by
deleting "Portable electronics transaction" and substituting "Portable electronics or optical
products transaction"; and by deleting "portable electronics" wherever it appears and
substituting "portable electronics or optical products".
SECTION 9. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101(10), is amended by
deleting "portable electronics transactions" and substituting "portable electronics or optical
products transactions".
SECTION 10. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1101, is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
( ) "Optical products" means smart glasses and non-electronic eyewear, and
includes prescription and non-prescription eyeglasses and sunglasses;
SECTION 11. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1102, is amended by deleting
"portable electronics" wherever it appears in subsections (a) and (b) and substituting "portable
electronics or optical products".
SECTION 12. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1103, is amended by deleting
"purchase or lease portable electronics or services" from subdivision (a)(2) and substituting
- 2 - 015411

"purchase or lease portable electronics, optical devices, or services"; and by deleting "portable
electronics" wherever it appears and substituting "portable electronics or optical products".
SECTION 13. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1104(a), is amended by
deleting "portable electronics" wherever it appears and substituting "portable electronics or
optical products".
SECTION 14. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1104(b)(1), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting:
(1) The charges for portable electronics or optical products insurance coverage
may be billed and collected by the vendor of portable electronics or optical products.
Any charge to the customer for coverage that is not included in the cost associated with
the purchase or lease of portable electronics, optical products, or related services must
be separately itemized on the enrolled customer's bill. If the portable electronics or
optical products insurance coverage is included with the purchase or lease of portable
electronics, optical products, or related services, then the vendor shall clearly and
conspicuously disclose to the enrolled customer that the coverage is included with the
purchase or lease of the portable electronics, optical products, or related services.
SECTION 15. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1104(b)(3), is amended by
deleting "portable electronics" and substituting "portable electronics or optical products".
SECTION 16. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1105, is amended by deleting
"portable electronics" wherever it appears and substituting "portable electronics or optical
products".
SECTION 17. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1106, is amended by deleting
"portable electronics" wherever it appears and substituting "portable electronics or optical
products".
SECTION 18. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-6-1107(d), is amended by
deleting "portable electronics" wherever it appears and substituting "portable electronics or
optical products".
- 3 - 015411

SECTION 19. The commissioner of commerce and insurance is authorized to
promulgate rules to effectuate this act. The rules must be promulgated in accordance with the
Uniform Administrative Procedures Act, compiled in Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4,
Chapter 5.
SECTION 20.
(a) For the purpose of rule promulgation, this act takes effect upon becoming a
law, the public welfare requiring it.
(b) For all other purposes:
(1) Sections 2-18 of this act take effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare
requiring it; and
(2) The remaining sections of this act take effect upon becoming a law,
the public welfare requiring it.
